self.name: messages.setInlineBotResults
self.description: Answer an inline query, for bots only
self.descriptionExcerpt: Answer an inline query, for bots only

arguments.name: gallery
arguments.description: Set this flag if the results are composed of media files

arguments.name: private
arguments.description: Set this flag if results may be cached on the server side only for the user that sent the query. By default, results may be returned to any user who sends the same query

arguments.name: results
arguments.description: Vector of results for the inline query

arguments.name: cacheTime
arguments.description: The maximum amount of time in seconds that the result of the inline query may be cached on the server. Defaults to 300.

arguments.name: nextOffset
arguments.description: Pass the offset that a client should send in the next query with the same text to receive more results. Pass an empty string if there are no more results or if you don‘t support pagination. Offset length can’t exceed 64 bytes.

arguments.name: switchPm
arguments.description: If passed, clients will display a button with specified text that switches the user to a private chat with the bot and sends the bot a start message with a certain parameter.

throws.description: The title of the article is empty

throws.description: The data of one or more of the buttons you provided is invalid
throws.name: BUTTON_DATA_INVALID

throws.description: The type of one or more of the buttons you provided is invalid
throws.name: BUTTON_TYPE_INVALID
